From: Michael Chan <michael.chan@broadcom.com>
Date: Mon, 12 Oct 2020 05:10:50 -0400
Subject: bnxt_en: Log event_data1 and event_data2 when handling RESET_NOTIFY
 event.
Patch-mainline: v5.10-rc1
Git-commit: c966c67c09921e117991b54a83e1e9ac6dbc3899
References: jsc#SLE-16649

Log these values that contain useful firmware state information.

Reviewed-by: Edwin Peer <edwin.peer@broadcom.com>
Reviewed-by: Vasundhara Volam <vasundhara-v.volam@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: Michael Chan <michael.chan@broadcom.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/1602493854-29283-6-git-send-email-michael.chan@broadcom.com
Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnxt/bnxt.c |    3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnxt/bnxt.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnxt/bnxt.c
@@ -2036,6 +2036,9 @@ static int bnxt_async_event_process(stru
 		set_bit(BNXT_RESET_TASK_SILENT_SP_EVENT, &bp->sp_event);
 		break;
 	case ASYNC_EVENT_CMPL_EVENT_ID_RESET_NOTIFY:
+		if (netif_msg_hw(bp))
+			netdev_warn(bp->dev, "Received RESET_NOTIFY event, data1: 0x%x, data2: 0x%x\n",
+				    data1, data2);
 		if (!bp->fw_health)
 			goto async_event_process_exit;
 
